      <aside class="calc-sidebar">
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h2>What is ideal weight?</h2>
          <p>Ideal weight is the weight range associated with good health for a given height and body frame. It is a reference point, not an absolute target. Body composition (muscle vs fat) matters more than the number on the scale.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>Which formula is most accurate?</summary>
            <p>No single formula is perfect for everyone. The Lorentz formula is most widely used in Europe. The BMI range (18.5–24.9) is the most commonly accepted medical reference worldwide.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Can I be healthy outside the ideal weight range?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Very muscular people may weigh more than the ideal range without excess body fat. These formulas are guidelines, not absolute rules.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Should I aim for the exact ideal weight?</summary>
            <p>Not necessarily. Aim for a healthy lifestyle — balanced diet, regular exercise, good sleep — rather than a specific number on the scale.</p>
